item.title: Crypto Bros’ Mistrial Was Such an ‘Emotional Burden’ for Deadlocked Jurors That ‘Half’ of Them Cried
item.description: It doesn't sound fun being a crypto juror.

item.title: ‘Pluribus’ May Not Be About AI, But Vince Gilligan Hates It Regardless
item.description: Unlike what happened with 'Breaking Bad,' Gilligan wants 'Pluribus' viewers to make their own conclusions on its themes.

item.title: I've spent a month with the iPhone 17 Pro, and it's confirmed my suspicions about Apple's new iPhone lineup
item.description: I've spent a month with the iPhone 17 Pro, and it's made me realize that I'm no longer 'pro' enough for Apple's best iPhones.

item.title: After testing this NAS device, Ugreen might have cornered the market for personal cloud services with the NASync DH2300
item.description: The Ugreen DH2300 is a basic two-bay NAS at a low price that makes it a great choice for home and small business users who need a Cloud backup device.

item.title: Microsoft built a fake online marketplace to see how its AI agents would work selling unsupervised - and let's just say the results were... unsurprising
item.description: Microsoft’s Magentic Marketplace shows AI tools still cannot reliably act independently in complex multi-agent simulations.

item.title: ‘Breaking Bad’ creator’s new show ‘Pluribus’ was emphatically ‘made by humans,’ not AI
item.description: If you watched all the way to the end of the new Apple TV show “Pluribus,” you may have noticed an unusual disclaimer in the credits: “This show was made by humans.”

item.title: Tesla Model Y pas chère, faillites dans le vélo, Renault Twingo – l’actu électrique de la semaine
item.description: De la Tesla Model Y à prix imbattable à l’explosion du marché des vélos électriques, en passant par la supercar BYD U9 frôlant les 500 km/h, le secteur électrique prouve qu’il ne dort jamais. Voici les sujets qui vous ont le plus passionnés ces derniers jours sur Survoltés.

item.title: What Is Dan Trachtenberg’s ‘Predator’ Trilogy About?
item.description: From 'Prey' to 'Killer of Killers' and now 'Badlands,' Trachtenberg may be using 'Predator' to drive a point home.
